[[File:Bad Wildbad Kurtheater 2008.jpg|thumb|The {{ill|Kurtheater Bad Wildbad|de|Kurtheater Bad Wildbad|lt=Königliche Kurtheater}} during Rossini in Wildbad, 2008]]
'''Rossini in Wildbad''' is a [[bel canto]] [[opera festival]] in [[Bad Wildbad]], [[Baden-Württemberg]], specialising in the lesser-known operas of [[Gioachino Rossini]] and his contemporaries.<ref>[http://www.rossini-in-wildbad.com/ Rossini in Wildbad Festival] website. Retrieved 25 December 2016.</ref>
The festival commemorates a stay by Rossini at the town's spa in 1856, which apparently invigorated him enough to start composing again.<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2012/07/25/arts/25iht-loomis25.html "Rossini and Contemporaries, Snuggly at Home in the Black Forest"], George Loomis, ''[[New York Times]]'', 24 July 2012</ref>
The festival was founded in 1989 by the conductor {{ill|Wilhelm Keitel (conductor)|de|Wilhelm Keitel (Dirigent)|lt=Wilhelm Keitel}}. {{clear right}}
